The paper deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) and focuses on managing self-interested agents to achieve optimal coordination. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves modeling and policy learning, which are subfields of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of contracts and rewards to incentivize agents falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
